140
01:24:49,609 --> 01:24:51,070
[SPEAKER_00]: Thank you everyone for today.

141
01:24:51,110 --> 01:24:57,371
[SPEAKER_00]: So as you see here on our next slide, we're just going to give a quick review of where we were in our last meeting and where we are now.

142
01:24:58,291 --> 01:25:01,432
[SPEAKER_00]: So originally, we had presented a preliminary budget of $89,933,398.

143
01:25:01,472 --> 01:25:04,093
[SPEAKER_00]: The city's original general fund budget allocation was $87,750,000, which gave us a variance

144
01:25:14,575 --> 01:25:14,675
[SPEAKER_00]: of $2,183,398.

145
01:25:14,735 --> 01:25:17,837
[SPEAKER_00]: After the finalization of the city's general budget of $89,100,000, we came to a variance of $833,398.

146
01:25:17,917 --> 01:25:22,761
[SPEAKER_00]: And over the next few slides, we'll talk about how we closed that gap to have a balanced budget.

147
01:25:40,915 --> 01:25:45,298
[SPEAKER_00]: So on this slide here, additional savings needed to close the remaining budget gap.

148
01:25:46,999 --> 01:25:53,004
[SPEAKER_00]: We ended up moving approximately, well we ended up moving $962,568.

149
01:25:53,664 --> 01:25:59,048
[SPEAKER_00]: And beneath that you'll see a summary of how we came to that number.

150
01:26:00,029 --> 01:26:06,814
[SPEAKER_00]: We're moving one special education coordinator to our fiscal year 26 circuit breaker.

151
01:26:08,883 --> 01:26:17,167
[SPEAKER_00]: We're reducing the math high school teaching staff by three, one in ELA, one in science, and one in world language.

152
01:26:17,908 --> 01:26:20,569
[SPEAKER_00]: These are all covered by retirement or non-renewals.

153
01:26:22,530 --> 01:26:30,934
[SPEAKER_00]: We're reducing the Medford High School vocational program by one early education staff member due to low enrollment.

154
01:26:31,534 --> 01:26:36,357
[SPEAKER_00]: The staff member will be transferred to an open vocational grant funded position.

155
01:26:37,901 --> 01:26:42,762
[SPEAKER_00]: So they will still be on the staff, but they will not be affecting our general ledger's budget line.

156
01:26:43,942 --> 01:26:54,765
[SPEAKER_00]: And the correct paraprofessional overstaffing over at the Brooks, we're reducing by four paras, three to be transferred to vocational programs and one non-renewal.

157
01:27:00,547 --> 01:27:02,367
[SPEAKER_00]: To continue on the narrative,

158
01:27:03,677 --> 01:27:07,259
[SPEAKER_00]: We're reducing one para at the Misita currently on workers competition.

159
01:27:08,380 --> 01:27:14,524
[SPEAKER_00]: The person who was filling in for that para on workers comp is currently, will still be funded.

160
01:27:15,785 --> 01:27:20,088
[SPEAKER_00]: We'll be discontinuing the para behavior specialist position over at the Brooks.

161
01:27:21,909 --> 01:27:25,771
[SPEAKER_00]: We're gonna discontinue a psychologist position funded in the Roberts.

162
01:27:26,932 --> 01:27:31,275
[SPEAKER_00]: This position will be shared between the McGlynn Elementary and the Roberts.

163
01:27:32,358 --> 01:27:39,722
[SPEAKER_00]: We're going to be reducing one academic support position at the high school currently assigned to the vocational program.

164
01:27:41,503 --> 01:27:48,967
[SPEAKER_00]: And also we found other areas of savings in non-unit salary schedules versus actual budget costs.

165
01:27:55,790 --> 01:27:58,112
[SPEAKER_19]: Yeah, just wanted to add that

166
01:27:59,330 --> 01:28:04,327
[SPEAKER_19]: you know, the teachers at the high school were a result of, you know,

167
01:28:06,589 --> 01:28:10,671
[SPEAKER_19]: We were informed by the schedule that was developed.

168
01:28:10,771 --> 01:28:14,733
[SPEAKER_19]: We did the, we did something different this year.

169
01:28:14,753 --> 01:28:31,462
[SPEAKER_19]: We scheduled the students first and so it's the case that all the sections are completely covered and we have three extra positions as a result and that work is actually continuing.

170
01:28:34,538 --> 01:28:41,900
[SPEAKER_19]: With the paras, we, you know, I guess what I would call it is position creep.

171
01:28:43,201 --> 01:28:59,646
[SPEAKER_19]: We had special ed director looked at the regulatory requirements for staffing and based on that, we can repurpose those paraprofessionals to other vacant positions.

172
01:29:04,518 --> 01:29:09,702
[SPEAKER_19]: We did also manage to get a few extra savings.

173
01:29:09,762 --> 01:29:13,545
[SPEAKER_19]: We get, we had the stadium mark for our vocational program ban.

174
01:29:14,726 --> 01:29:19,049
[SPEAKER_19]: So we'll be able to save $50,000 in our budget for that.

175
01:29:19,930 --> 01:29:27,576
[SPEAKER_19]: We reduced slightly the asks from the academic directors.

176
01:29:28,917 --> 01:29:40,711
[SPEAKER_19]: for supplies and materials that covered challenge courses, electives, high quality instructional materials, things like that.

177
01:29:40,771 --> 01:29:45,516
[SPEAKER_19]: So they still will have a sufficient budget to make those purchases.

178
01:29:47,363 --> 01:29:54,728
[SPEAKER_19]: And then we were able to reduce the waste management account.

