260
01:36:35,504 --> 01:36:43,394
[SPEAKER_10]: We are reverting back to superintendent's report number two, Roberts Elementary School HVAC project update and recommendation to approve.

261
01:36:44,075 --> 01:36:47,579
[SPEAKER_10]: RFS engineering and Mr. Ken Lord, chief operations officer, to present.

262
01:36:48,259 --> 01:36:48,540
[SPEAKER_10]: Welcome.

263
01:36:50,012 --> 01:36:50,332
[SPEAKER_18]: Thank you.

264
01:36:50,993 --> 01:36:59,363
[SPEAKER_18]: So tonight we're going to hear the feasibility study and options for the Roberts Accelerator Repair Program for HVAC and roof replacement.

265
01:36:59,443 --> 01:37:02,426
[SPEAKER_18]: Brian LaRoche from PCA 360 here is going to do most of the presentation.

266
01:37:02,467 --> 01:37:03,308
[SPEAKER_18]: He can introduce his team.

267
01:37:05,888 --> 01:37:07,468
[SPEAKER_22]: Thanks very much for having us tonight.

268
01:37:08,109 --> 01:37:09,309
[SPEAKER_22]: And again, I'm with PCA 360.

269
01:37:09,709 --> 01:37:11,950
[SPEAKER_22]: We're the OPMs for the project.

270
01:37:12,910 --> 01:37:20,272
[SPEAKER_22]: So this Roberts Elementary School project is partially being funded through the MSBA Accelerated Repair Program.

271
01:37:21,372 --> 01:37:25,813
[SPEAKER_22]: So I know that you had a presentation just recently on the new high school, which is their core program.

272
01:37:25,853 --> 01:37:28,114
[SPEAKER_22]: So this is a little different than the high school project.

273
01:37:29,151 --> 01:37:33,473
[SPEAKER_22]: So, the accelerated repair program follows slightly different parameters.

274
01:37:34,314 --> 01:37:37,275
[SPEAKER_22]: So, we'll get into a little bit of that as we go through the presentation.

275
01:37:37,295 --> 01:37:40,877
[SPEAKER_22]: So, we're very early, if you could go to the next slide.

276
01:37:42,317 --> 01:37:44,999
[SPEAKER_22]: We're very early in the process with the MSBA.

277
01:37:45,339 --> 01:37:58,325
[SPEAKER_22]: And so, in this particular program, in the beginning, we have to study three options for how we're going to replace the HVAC systems and electrify the building, basically using heat pump technology.

278
01:37:59,283 --> 01:38:06,387
[SPEAKER_22]: So we have completed the initial study of the building and then looked to see what would be appropriate for the three options.

279
01:38:06,947 --> 01:38:09,088
[SPEAKER_22]: So we're presenting them to you tonight.

280
01:38:10,289 --> 01:38:18,113
[SPEAKER_22]: And the idea is after tonight we'll, or I guess you have a little bit more time, maybe a week or so, when we hear your decision,

281
01:38:19,099 --> 01:38:24,105
[SPEAKER_22]: We're going to take that one design and develop it up to the schematic design level.

282
01:38:24,685 --> 01:38:32,955
[SPEAKER_22]: The MSBA, before we submit to the MSBA board, requires that we've selected one option and we've developed it to schematic level.

283
01:38:33,195 --> 01:38:35,858
[SPEAKER_22]: So tonight, you're seeing feasibility.

284
01:38:36,648 --> 01:38:37,950
[SPEAKER_22]: Very early in the design.

285
01:38:37,990 --> 01:38:40,813
[SPEAKER_22]: We've only really been in the process for about six weeks.

286
01:38:42,114 --> 01:38:43,776
[SPEAKER_22]: And so that's where we're at right now.

287
01:38:43,956 --> 01:38:48,321
[SPEAKER_22]: In the MSBA flowchart, the red star, you can see where we're at in the process.

288
01:38:49,081 --> 01:38:54,027
[SPEAKER_22]: So in the, as we move forward through the project, we'll move into

289
01:38:54,867 --> 01:38:58,109
[SPEAKER_22]: funding the project, and that's really a two-part process.

290
01:38:58,469 --> 01:39:03,311
[SPEAKER_22]: The first part is we present the schematic design package to the MSBA board.

291
01:39:03,752 --> 01:39:07,974
[SPEAKER_22]: That will happen at the end of August for the October 28th board meeting.

292
01:39:09,094 --> 01:39:16,177
[SPEAKER_22]: And then once the board then votes, then they'll kick it back to the city to appropriate the funds for the project.

293
01:39:16,718 --> 01:39:22,901
[SPEAKER_22]: And then once the city has appropriated the funds, then we will be able to move into the detailed design.

294
01:39:24,122 --> 01:39:26,925
[SPEAKER_22]: So I'll tell you a little bit more about schedule.

295
01:39:26,945 --> 01:39:28,306
[SPEAKER_22]: If you could go to the next slide, please.

296
01:39:30,309 --> 01:39:36,456
[SPEAKER_22]: As you can see from here, as I mentioned, we're in the early phase of the project feasibility slash schematic design.

297
01:39:37,793 --> 01:39:43,297
[SPEAKER_22]: And we have, we'll be before you again before we finalize this scope.

298
01:39:43,757 --> 01:39:50,061
[SPEAKER_22]: We'll come back with the schematic design presentation and ask for your approval before we make a submission to the MSBA.

299
01:39:50,762 --> 01:39:55,285
[SPEAKER_22]: So that will be happening mid-August when we'll come before you.

300
01:39:55,305 --> 01:39:57,346
[SPEAKER_22]: So that will have to be scheduled.

301
01:39:58,222 --> 01:40:04,726
[SPEAKER_22]: And then after that, like I said, we would go through these approval process between the MSBA and the city.

302
01:40:05,166 --> 01:40:06,847
[SPEAKER_22]: That takes us to about the first of the year.

303
01:40:07,388 --> 01:40:14,512
[SPEAKER_22]: And then right at the beginning of the first of the year, we're going to develop the design to a level we can go out to bid for the project.

304
01:40:15,350 --> 01:40:22,554
[SPEAKER_22]: The goal for our project is we want to get your project out to bid and awarded with plenty of time so that we can use summer 27.

305
01:40:23,855 --> 01:40:31,220
[SPEAKER_22]: There's quite a long process of getting through submittals and shop drawings and ordering equipment and so forth before we can do anything in the field.

306
01:40:32,160 --> 01:40:41,346
[SPEAKER_22]: The summers are extremely short, and we have to make sure that we have all of the planning in place well in advance to make sure that we make the summer a success.

307
01:40:42,186 --> 01:40:48,250
[SPEAKER_22]: So we see this project as a two-summer project, and we have two options to present to you.

308
01:40:49,111 --> 01:40:56,315
[SPEAKER_22]: Each one is a little bit different in terms of its timing, and again, we'll get into that a little bit as we get further into the presentation.

309
01:40:57,394 --> 01:41:02,125
[SPEAKER_22]: So with that, I just want to talk slightly about the accelerated repair program.

310
01:41:02,145 --> 01:41:02,968
[SPEAKER_22]: So next slide, please.

311
01:41:05,676 --> 01:41:16,125
[SPEAKER_22]: I know I watched the presentation that was made to you and it was a discussion about how the MSBA reimburses in a core project and, you know, what's the effective reimbursement rate.

312
01:41:16,826 --> 01:41:22,190
[SPEAKER_22]: On an accelerated repair project, there aren't as many exclusions to the project.

313
01:41:22,290 --> 01:41:25,473
[SPEAKER_22]: So, I know your reimbursement rate from the MSBA is 53.32.

314
01:41:29,350 --> 01:41:43,115
[SPEAKER_22]: You know, there will be probably a few things will be exempt, but generally speaking, if we stay with the program of replacing the HVAC systems and the roof and making the ADA upgrades, it's generally all reimbursable.

315
01:41:43,195 --> 01:41:44,836
[SPEAKER_22]: So that's the good news about this project.

316
01:41:45,396 --> 01:41:48,178
[SPEAKER_22]: It's only if we start adding on other scopes.

317
01:41:48,818 --> 01:41:56,683
[SPEAKER_22]: For example, I know it might come up tonight, if we add solar to this design team's scope, the MSBA wouldn't reimburse for that.

318
01:41:57,284 --> 01:41:59,105
[SPEAKER_22]: But it certainly could be part of the project.

319
01:41:59,165 --> 01:42:07,230
[SPEAKER_22]: So what we're presenting to you tonight is largely all part of the program following the requirements.

320
01:42:07,791 --> 01:42:10,052
[SPEAKER_22]: So everything is pretty much reimbursable.

321
01:42:10,392 --> 01:42:14,335
[SPEAKER_22]: Change orders, of course, with the MSBA are subject to their final approval.

322
01:42:15,888 --> 01:42:29,218
[SPEAKER_22]: Anyhow, so the, again, you're getting a very good reimbursement rate of 53.32, and with that, I just would like to talk to you briefly about the scope before I turn it over to our engineering team.

323
01:42:30,119 --> 01:42:36,424
[SPEAKER_22]: So as I mentioned, it's roof replacement is part of this, and because of the size of the project,

324
01:42:37,390 --> 01:42:39,595
[SPEAKER_22]: we will trigger ADA compliance.

325
01:42:40,196 --> 01:42:41,599
[SPEAKER_22]: The building is not that old.

326
01:42:41,679 --> 01:42:44,184
[SPEAKER_22]: It was built in or opened in 2003.

327
01:42:44,224 --> 01:42:45,326
[SPEAKER_22]: So at that time we had ADA.

328
01:42:48,365 --> 01:43:00,275
[SPEAKER_22]: So, the building is basically compliant, but we did have a code consultant go through the building, and they did an extensive evaluation, and there are a few things that we do have to do.

329
01:43:00,295 --> 01:43:02,457
[SPEAKER_22]: You know, there's a coat hook in the wrong spot.

330
01:43:02,517 --> 01:43:03,498
[SPEAKER_22]: The mirror's too high.

331
01:43:03,538 --> 01:43:05,479
[SPEAKER_22]: The toilet's a little bit too close to the wall.

332
01:43:05,520 --> 01:43:08,042
[SPEAKER_22]: So, those are the types of things that we have to do.

333
01:43:08,582 --> 01:43:14,126
[SPEAKER_22]: And in all, they amount to about 500,000 for a building of that size is really not significant.

334
01:43:14,967 --> 01:43:18,630
[SPEAKER_22]: So the good news is we're not adding an elevator or anything sizable like that.

335
01:43:18,670 --> 01:43:20,271
[SPEAKER_22]: These are all fairly small moves.

336
01:43:21,492 --> 01:43:24,714
[SPEAKER_22]: And then, so on the roof, let me just touch a little bit on that.

337
01:43:25,335 --> 01:43:32,140
[SPEAKER_22]: So the existing EPDM roof is at its end of its useful life, so it needs to be replaced.

338
01:43:32,720 --> 01:43:35,502
[SPEAKER_22]: So we do have options on the roof replacement.

339
01:43:36,183 --> 01:43:41,187
[SPEAKER_22]: The MSBA asks us to look at a recoat, which gets you about 10 years more of life.

340
01:43:41,767 --> 01:43:47,892
[SPEAKER_22]: But we know that the city wants to move forward with solar, so we know that that's not a viable option for you.

341
01:43:48,353 --> 01:43:52,276
[SPEAKER_22]: And so when we present the schematic design package to the MSBA, we'll let them know that.

342
01:43:52,926 --> 01:44:02,116
[SPEAKER_22]: If we're putting solar in the roof, which I know you want, and that's a goal of the city, we need a new roof on there that's going to have the full life of the roof before you put solar.

343
01:44:02,176 --> 01:44:08,783
[SPEAKER_22]: That way the roof warranty and the solar system match in terms of how long that they can be on the roof.

344
01:44:09,503 --> 01:44:13,428
[SPEAKER_22]: So what we'll present to you in the budget later on is a roof replacement.

345
01:44:14,249 --> 01:44:19,414
[SPEAKER_22]: with a PVC system, 80 mil because that's what solar needs.

346
01:44:20,416 --> 01:44:24,160
[SPEAKER_22]: So that is already baked into the scope of what we're considering at the moment.

347
01:44:25,261 --> 01:44:31,268
[SPEAKER_22]: Then we get into the HVAC and our team from RISC Frost Engineering is going to go through that in detail.

348
01:44:31,708 --> 01:44:34,732
[SPEAKER_22]: The only other thing that we're as a team looking at is

349
01:44:36,208 --> 01:44:49,614
[SPEAKER_22]: making the building future ready for full electrification, making sure that we're sizing the electrical service so that as time moves on, that the work we do now is set the building up for that.

350
01:44:49,734 --> 01:44:52,095
[SPEAKER_22]: So we'll get into that a little bit more in the presentation.

351
01:44:53,155 --> 01:44:56,757
[SPEAKER_22]: So with that, I am going to turn over the presentation.

352
01:44:57,537 --> 01:45:05,100
[SPEAKER_22]: Just a moment, if the RISC4AST team want to come up, I'll just finish with the next slide on the roof just to give an overview of the project.

353
01:45:06,435 --> 01:45:15,380
[SPEAKER_22]: So the school here, aerial view you see, on the left corner, there is already an existing mechanical well in the building.

354
01:45:15,740 --> 01:45:22,044
[SPEAKER_22]: So all of the equipment, the rooftop equipment, is inside this enclosure, which is an acoustic enclosure.

355
01:45:22,484 --> 01:45:26,626
[SPEAKER_22]: So that's something that's gonna come up in our presentation that we'll talk about a little bit later.

356
01:45:27,306 --> 01:45:31,909
[SPEAKER_22]: There's an option where all the equipment fits in with this existing infrastructure.

357
01:45:32,529 --> 01:45:41,815
[SPEAKER_22]: And then there's a third option where the equipment has to go in the higher roof and now we get into considerations with noise in making sure that we address that in the project.

358
01:45:42,696 --> 01:45:47,840
[SPEAKER_22]: But we're looking at replacing entirely all of the black area with new roofing systems.

359
01:45:48,640 --> 01:45:50,281
[SPEAKER_22]: And if you could go over to the next slide.

360
01:45:52,603 --> 01:45:58,008
[SPEAKER_22]: I talked just briefly about some of this, but as I said, the roof is at its end of its useful life.

361
01:45:58,669 --> 01:46:05,956
[SPEAKER_22]: Edge flashings, especially that well that I was just describing with the mechanical equipment, there's a lot of active leaking.

362
01:46:06,616 --> 01:46:16,946
[SPEAKER_22]: The roof has been infrared studied, so we know there are some points of failure even on the upper roof where roof insulation has gotten wet, and there's quite a bit of it.

363
01:46:17,965 --> 01:46:26,853
[SPEAKER_22]: So when we move into the next phase, we'll be looking at options of whether we can reuse and augment any of the insulation to save money.

364
01:46:27,334 --> 01:46:30,557
[SPEAKER_22]: And that's something we'll be studying a little bit further as we get into this.

365
01:46:31,237 --> 01:46:37,563
[SPEAKER_22]: But for the moment, what we're presenting to you tonight assumes a full roof replacement, including the insulation.

366
01:46:38,104 --> 01:46:41,747
[SPEAKER_22]: That way we can get down to the roof deck and put in the proper membrane.

367
01:46:42,608 --> 01:46:44,089
[SPEAKER_22]: for vapor control.

368
01:46:45,230 --> 01:46:47,351
[SPEAKER_22]: So that's what we're considering right now.

369
01:46:47,852 --> 01:46:52,055
[SPEAKER_22]: And next slide, we can kind of briefly go right through.

370
01:46:52,075 --> 01:46:54,417
[SPEAKER_22]: I already talked about code compliance.

371
01:46:54,977 --> 01:46:56,358
[SPEAKER_22]: It's largely ADA.

372
01:46:57,159 --> 01:47:04,044
[SPEAKER_22]: Because of the scale of the project and the assessed value of the building, we exceed 30% threshold.

373
01:47:04,525 --> 01:47:08,248
[SPEAKER_22]: And at that, we have to look at full compliance with accessibility.

374
01:47:08,988 --> 01:47:10,449
[SPEAKER_22]: So that's why we're considering it.

375
01:47:11,988 --> 01:47:12,188
[SPEAKER_22]: Okay.

