483
01:57:42,812 --> 01:57:43,612
[SPEAKER_03]: That's the intent.

484
01:57:45,710 --> 01:57:53,196
[SPEAKER_03]: both refrigerant and water pipes will go into the building to serve, you know, miscellaneous terminal heating and cooling devices.

485
01:57:55,218 --> 01:58:02,704
[SPEAKER_03]: This will also include replacing the existing units with package rooftop units, air source heat pumps.

486
01:58:04,105 --> 01:58:06,567
[SPEAKER_03]: That will also have energy recovery.

487
01:58:11,061 --> 01:58:17,621
[SPEAKER_03]: There will be a backup option required for the air to water source heat pump, so we will be using boilers for that.

488
01:58:20,187 --> 01:58:38,418
[SPEAKER_03]: The terminal units for this option, we will have new unit heaters, new VAV boxes, new radiators, and then most of the cooling and heating for majority of the spaces will be done through VRF style ceiling cassettes and that sort of thing.

