508
02:01:06,576 --> 02:01:17,105
[SPEAKER_21]: which will come out to about 250,000 to 285,000 kilowatt hours per year, which will offset the utility costs about 10, 15% for the school.

509
02:01:18,166 --> 02:01:24,911
[SPEAKER_21]: This will also offset about 20 to 25% of the emissions as well, eventually when we move on to the PV.

510
02:01:26,413 --> 02:01:32,758
[SPEAKER_21]: And then on the right is if we decide to go with a option three, which would be

511
02:01:34,252 --> 02:01:36,613
