546
02:05:51,979 --> 02:05:58,062
[SPEAKER_17]: So you'll see all the systems, the heat pump systems, are far more efficient than the existing system.

547
02:05:58,983 --> 02:06:09,830
[SPEAKER_17]: And they're all in the same order of magnitude, which is 40% to 50% less than the existing system.

548
02:06:10,850 --> 02:06:12,031
[SPEAKER_17]: So in the next slide.

549
02:06:14,160 --> 02:06:16,881
[SPEAKER_17]: is calculating the CO2 emissions.

550
02:06:16,901 --> 02:06:24,425
[SPEAKER_17]: You see this is not directly analogous to the energy use intensity.

551
02:06:25,045 --> 02:06:26,646
[SPEAKER_17]: This is specific to carbon.

552
02:06:28,327 --> 02:06:36,991
[SPEAKER_17]: So again, all options will be a significant reduction from the existing system.

