02:24:07,946 --> 02:24:13,048
[SPEAKER_22]: No, our expectation is the life expectancy of the system when it's complete will be the same across all of them.

730
02:24:13,068 --> 02:24:15,890
[SPEAKER_07]: Do you have a sense of what that expectancy is?

731
02:24:16,645 --> 02:24:16,805
[SPEAKER_07]: Yeah.

732
02:24:17,406 --> 02:24:32,283
[SPEAKER_03]: So we, in the life cycle cost analysis, what we've tried to measure is that about 25% of your equipment would be expected to be replaced in 15 years.

733
02:24:33,204 --> 02:24:36,628
[SPEAKER_03]: And then in 25 years, all of it will need to be replaced.

734
02:24:37,522 --> 02:24:46,545
[SPEAKER_03]: And the only exception to that is that in the geothermal system, and that's why the bar was lower, is that you don't need to replace the well field.

735
02:24:46,565 --> 02:24:49,345
[SPEAKER_03]: The well field's life expectancy is 50 years.

736
02:24:50,026 --> 02:24:54,887
[SPEAKER_03]: But as far as the heat pump technology, the indoor or outdoor equipment,

737
02:24:55,697 --> 02:24:57,739
[SPEAKER_03]: it's anywhere from 15 to 25 years.

738
02:24:58,079 --> 02:25:12,609
[SPEAKER_03]: They vary, everything varies, so it's hard to just put one number to it, but that's why we estimate that historically it's 25% of it gets replaced in 15 years, and then everything gets replaced in 25.

739
02:25:12,909 --> 02:25:18,353
[SPEAKER_03]: In current systems right now, it's almost at the end of their life expectancy.

740
02:25:18,413 --> 02:25:24,438
[SPEAKER_07]: Thank you, that's really helpful for fitting into the context of other work we're doing in the district and then across the city as well, so thank you.

741
02:25:29,177 --> 02:25:31,479
[SPEAKER_10]: Member Russo, then Member Parks, then Leo.

742
02:25:33,781 --> 02:25:34,902
[SPEAKER_04]: Thank you for the presentation.

743
02:25:34,922 --> 02:25:48,273
[SPEAKER_04]: I did read it ahead of time and I've been the geothermal or die guy for a while now, but I'm definitely going to make a motion to choose option one.

744
02:25:49,855 --> 02:25:50,195
[SPEAKER_04]: Thank you.

745
02:25:55,499 --> 02:25:56,060
[SPEAKER_10]: Member Parks.

746
02:25:58,019 --> 02:25:59,240
