754
02:26:40,718 --> 02:26:43,900
[SPEAKER_06]: Okay, so you modeled using electric as your backup?

755
02:26:43,920 --> 02:26:45,482
[SPEAKER_22]: Correct, electric backup boiler.

756
02:26:45,522 --> 02:26:46,342
[SPEAKER_06]: Okay, perfect.

757
02:26:47,103 --> 02:26:57,852
[SPEAKER_06]: And then, so that was factored into the pricing for these, is buying a new electric boiler, not reusing the old gas boiler, as it said in, I think it said in one of the slides or something.

758
02:26:58,325 --> 02:27:03,086
[SPEAKER_03]: Yeah, the modeling is assumed all options electric boiler.

759
02:27:03,366 --> 02:27:04,126
[SPEAKER_06]: OK, perfect.

760
02:27:04,246 --> 02:27:05,447
[SPEAKER_06]: That was one of my questions.

761
02:27:06,207 --> 02:27:15,649
[SPEAKER_06]: The other one is in terms, you noted that you're installing empty conduits for the PV.

762
02:27:16,269 --> 02:27:21,330
