764
02:27:27,589 --> 02:27:32,627
[SPEAKER_06]: Dealing with that, have you ever considered installing the footings for the panels?

765
02:27:34,758 --> 02:27:43,883
[SPEAKER_22]: The reason that we were looking at 80 mil roofing membrane is so that it could be a ballasted system so that you wouldn't have to put any penetrations through the roof.

766
02:27:44,763 --> 02:27:57,789
[SPEAKER_22]: So the recovery board underneath the roof would be designed with a higher density anticipating the solar, but our goal would be not to penetrate that roof with the new solar system.

767
02:27:57,829 --> 02:27:58,690
[SPEAKER_22]: Perfect, thank you.

768
02:27:58,950 --> 02:28:01,131
[SPEAKER_17]: We did verify the roof capacity.

769
02:28:02,225 --> 02:28:15,428
[SPEAKER_17]: So how much existing weight it could support and the accounted for in the estimate, reinforcing the areas that did not have sufficient capacity to support a ballasted PV system in the future.

770
02:28:16,028 --> 02:28:16,228
Okay.

771
02:28:16,448 --> 02:28:16,788
[SPEAKER_06]: Thank you.

772
02:28:16,968 --> 02:28:21,989
[SPEAKER_06]: And then my last question, just as a last ditch effort for the geothermal.

773
02:28:22,770 --> 02:28:29,351
