779
02:29:06,449 --> 02:29:08,250
[SPEAKER_22]: So we put the question to them today.

780
02:29:08,310 --> 02:29:11,153
[SPEAKER_22]: We haven't gotten an answer back.

781
02:29:12,514 --> 02:29:15,837
[SPEAKER_22]: It's possible, but we don't know the answer of how they would

782
02:29:16,713 --> 02:29:21,195
[SPEAKER_22]: would they fund and reimburse a system off school property?

783
02:29:22,456 --> 02:29:28,738
[SPEAKER_22]: One of the things as I was trying to kind of work through my job is to find what are the challenges, right?

784
02:29:30,139 --> 02:29:34,901
[SPEAKER_22]: One of the challenges for me, we're just finishing a school project now where

785
02:29:35,580 --> 02:29:38,381
[SPEAKER_22]: We put geothermal under an adjacent parkland.

786
02:29:39,261 --> 02:29:45,422
[SPEAKER_22]: And so Article 97 talks about parkland, but this is under.

787
02:29:46,002 --> 02:29:57,184
[SPEAKER_22]: So we didn't have to go to legislature to get any special approval, but we had to essentially go through like a license agreement with whatever authority had control of that park.

788
02:29:57,945 --> 02:30:04,526
[SPEAKER_22]: So the MSBA wouldn't even entertain our schematic design until all of those legal questions had been resolved.

789
02:30:05,406 --> 02:30:11,127
[SPEAKER_22]: So, again, me just trying to anticipate what are the challenges, I think it's a fantastic idea.

790
02:30:11,147 --> 02:30:13,628
[SPEAKER_22]: I think that time might get us.

791
02:30:14,408 --> 02:30:29,292
[SPEAKER_22]: I think that, you know, so what we have modeled for you right now is that we're going to submit to the MSBA in late August to be on their October 28th hearing so that we can come before the city for funding, to be out to bid, whatever.

792
02:30:29,312 --> 02:30:29,652
[SPEAKER_22]: I know.

793
02:30:30,112 --> 02:30:33,193
[SPEAKER_22]: I think, so the MSBA only meets every two months.

794
02:30:34,477 --> 02:30:39,641
[SPEAKER_22]: So if we miss that deadline, and then we're two months later, say, we've missed summer 27.

795
02:30:40,581 --> 02:30:57,273
[SPEAKER_22]: So honestly, I think it's a phenomenal idea, because the biggest challenge with option two is it takes about five months to do all of the preparation, put the wells in, get all your circuiting, all your piping back, restore.

796
02:30:58,094 --> 02:31:00,335
[SPEAKER_22]: And we don't have five months in the summertime.

797
02:31:00,435 --> 02:31:05,176
[SPEAKER_22]: So we would be impacting the school year or, you know, monthly phasing.

798
02:31:05,236 --> 02:31:06,636
[SPEAKER_22]: And then it adds costs to the project.

799
02:31:06,676 --> 02:31:08,877
[SPEAKER_22]: So I liked your idea.

800
02:31:08,897 --> 02:31:09,897
[SPEAKER_22]: I thought it was fantastic.

801
02:31:10,338 --> 02:31:12,898
[SPEAKER_22]: So we did pose the question, the MSBA, would they reimburse?

