972
02:44:49,925 --> 02:44:57,268
[SPEAKER_09]: The two kind of hanging pieces to highlight for this evening, and then I'm happy to take any questions, would be

973
02:44:58,489 --> 02:45:00,830
[SPEAKER_09]: when it comes to the elementary recess.

974
02:45:01,450 --> 02:45:07,172
[SPEAKER_09]: So the following language was put in all of the four elementary handbooks.

975
02:45:07,472 --> 02:45:15,555
[SPEAKER_09]: It says, recess is an essential component of a child's physical, social, and emotional development and will not be withheld as a disciplinary measure.

976
02:45:16,155 --> 02:45:20,557
[SPEAKER_09]: Consequences must be logical, timely, and linked directly to the incident or infraction.

977
02:45:21,517 --> 02:45:33,953
[SPEAKER_09]: This commitment is structurally reinforced and visible across three distinct practices currently outlined within the elementary handbooks, parentheses, discipline code, recess expectations, and homework expectations.

978
02:45:34,714 --> 02:45:36,657
[SPEAKER_09]: Within the discipline code, there is

979
02:45:37,798 --> 02:45:48,801
[SPEAKER_09]: A footnote or an asterisk next for number three where it says for serious conduct violations, it may result in the loss of building privileges.

980
02:45:48,901 --> 02:45:53,583
[SPEAKER_09]: For example, assemblies, recess, intramurals, field trips, extracurricular activities.

981
02:45:54,463 --> 02:46:07,942
[SPEAKER_09]: That footnote on recess, this next statement has been added in all of the handbooks that says, please note that the loss of recess requires school leader, which is a principal or assistant principal approval.

982
02:46:08,876 --> 02:46:20,349
[SPEAKER_09]: So if there is an incident in which there is some sort of discipline issue that has arrived, recess cannot be taken away without the approval of the principal or the assistant principal.

983
02:46:21,350 --> 02:46:25,095
[SPEAKER_09]: There is no change to the recess expectations as

984
02:46:27,598 --> 02:46:45,873
[SPEAKER_09]: It was in there before that it is the expectation that students have their recess, but if a child displays unsafe behaviors while at recess, their time may be limited or taken away as a logical consequence, which is really just a time for the child to regain composure.

985
02:46:47,125 --> 02:47:01,097
[SPEAKER_09]: There also is not a change to homework expectations as there is clear language, although we did bold the sentence in the middle of the homework expectations that says homework incompletion will not result in the loss of recess.

986
02:47:02,679 --> 02:47:10,345
[SPEAKER_09]: We're hoping this adds clarity to the position that we all hold dear around recess time.

