1094
03:00:13,858 --> 03:00:17,020
[SPEAKER_09]: And some more information, for example, on the seal of biliteracy.

1095
03:00:18,201 --> 03:00:32,392
[SPEAKER_09]: Addition to descriptions for non-Chapter 74 technology, curriculum, program needs, media and technology, digital art, scene shop, slash stage craft, et cetera, as requested by the MSBA.

1096
03:00:33,413 --> 03:00:46,887
[SPEAKER_09]: And additionally, minor revisions to language surrounding black box drama and engineering robotics courses, non-CTE to incorporate decisions from, as Rosemary said, the April 27th SBC meeting.

1097
03:00:47,548 --> 03:00:50,912
[SPEAKER_09]: Those last two bullet points really kind of come down to

1098
03:00:52,874 --> 03:00:57,562
[SPEAKER_09]: How we approach this which is reduce redundancies and approve efficiencies.

1099
03:00:58,163 --> 03:01:03,111
[SPEAKER_09]: And so as we said at the SBC meeting as well as to this committee before.

1100
03:01:04,664 --> 03:01:14,826
[SPEAKER_09]: Our goal is to make sure we're creating flexible, adaptable, multi-use spaces that can grow with the needs of education as well as the needs of the community.

1101
03:01:15,387 --> 03:01:23,969
[SPEAKER_09]: We don't know what education is going to look like years from now, and so really creating spaces that are multi-purpose and flexible was the key.

1102
03:01:25,289 --> 03:01:30,890
[SPEAKER_09]: MSBA requires that each space is used 85% of the time each day.

1103
03:01:31,550 --> 03:01:34,011
[SPEAKER_09]: So when we're looking at something like a black box,

1104
03:01:35,512 --> 03:01:46,541
[SPEAKER_09]: We're not going to remove the black box, but having a standalone black box may not check the box to be used 85% of the time each day.

1105
03:01:46,942 --> 03:01:59,692
[SPEAKER_09]: However, really monopolizing on large group instructional spaces would be the key so that we could create a black box within a large group instructional space.

1106
03:02:00,593 --> 03:02:13,403
[SPEAKER_09]: for the use of black box purposes, for performances, for presentations, for science activities, whatever someone wants to use a black box for.

1107
03:02:17,715 --> 03:02:21,418
[SPEAKER_09]: Next slide, I hope that, if there are any questions, please let me know.

1108
03:02:22,159 --> 03:02:35,469
[SPEAKER_09]: Then the other piece that I presented along with the team on that April 27th meeting was our approach to what we had three buckets and we said repurpose.

